<br>
If you are in a situation where those slight differences aren't necessary (like just about every xp grind) then the benefits that a paladin brings to the group so far outweigh the penalties that it is pathetic. If the paladin happens to have some sort of mana regen the gulf widens dramatically.<br>
<br>
I honestly think that paladins are borderline overpowered in xp groups. <br>
<br>
As far as comparing PAL vs SHD for xp groups, it is almost entirely dependant on equipment and player skill. Paladins and shadow knight's have probably the closest parity of any 2 classes in the game. A well equipped, well played SK is just as powerful as a well equipped, well played paladin. There will be situations where each is slightly better than the other. The tools each class has are different but very comparable. Both of those 2 characters (well equipped and well played) are 2 of the most powerful xp group characters in the game.<br>
<br>
I'm glad some of you found my initial response amusing. Keep in mind, it isn't your job to edjumuhkate complete strangers on the dynamics and nuances of the game. If they don't know any better, let them suffer because of their prejudice and closed mindedness.<br>
<br>
